<TITLE> Khagrachharhi OC removed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, Mar 4 (bdnews24.com)  Khagrachharhi Sadar police chief Mohammed Shahriar Khan has been stand released days after bloody clashes between Bangali settlers and indigenous people in the hills town. He has been asked to join the Rajshahi police range by Thursday. The police administration assigned no reason for the order. Khagrachharhi police superintendent Abu Kalam Siddiqui told reporters that Mohammed Kamrul Islam had taken the charge of the police station for the time being. Islam was transferred from Dhaka Metropolitan Police in recent times. Shahriar Khan told bdnews24.com that he was transferred in line with the government rule. At least one person was killed during clashes between indigenous and settler communities in Khagrachharhi on Feb 23 following clashes in another hill district Rangamati. Authorities imposed section 144 in the district for five days there since after the incident. bd
